subclause.relationship_to_base_verdict_n1_e:
Base verdict n1(e) Part 2 already handles fresh-shell User-scope fallback INSIDE Item 4.3:
```powershell
if (-not $env:VIKUNJA_TOKEN) {
  $userToken = [Environment]::GetEnvironmentVariable('VIKUNJA_TOKEN', 'User')
  if ($userToken) {
    $env:VIKUNJA_TOKEN = $userToken
    Write-Host "VIKUNJA_TOKEN loaded from User-scope env (fresh-shell fallback)."
  } else { ... REST user/pass fallback ... }
}
```

That handles the "EA-8 reaches Item 4.3 without token" case. This supplement adds a Part 0 that performs the same load EARLIER — as the FIRST EA-8 terminal action, before any other Stage 4 command. Reasons:
- Eliminates any pre-Item-4.3 command that might silently depend on VIKUNJA_TOKEN being present (e.g., diagnostic invocations, REST-based smoke checks).
- Surfaces the "token not in User scope either" case immediately, allowing LA to set it before destructive cutover begins.
- Mirrors the LA-prescribed EA-8 init pointer first-action ordering (see §init_pointer_first_action_directive below).
